choices.text:
the demise of dictatorship, where you witness the masses come together to demand an end to dictatorial rule in African nation. We don’t know where this is heading, and it is too early to tell, we can all agree that this is definitely not going to stop, but Arab Spring is still unfolding in the middle east.

And that brings me to this speech, is it so wrong to voice out free speech?

I’m not really one for politics and religion but this kinda political speech speaks what obviously needs to be said. Here’s an excerpt from the speech:

Even though these [the Jews] have no link with that country, they are trying to claim it and through money and fraud they are endeavouring to purchase Arabic areas. Even today, all that is happening there are intelligent measures taken by the Zionists to occupy all the land of Palestine, not excluding one sign, not excluding one house.
